<span class="cp">#define <a href="v6.0/C/ident/pr_fmt">pr_fmt</a>(<a href="v6.0/C/ident/fmt">fmt</a>) <a href="v6.0/C/ident/KBUILD_MODNAME">KBUILD_MODNAME</a> &quot;: &quot; <a href="v6.0/C/ident/FORMAT">FORMAT</a>(<a href="v6.0/C/ident/fmt">fmt</a>)</span>

<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/file.h">linux/file.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/fs.h">linux/fs.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/list.h">linux/list.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/math64.h">linux/math64.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/mm.h">linux/mm.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/mutex.h">linux/mutex.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/poll.h">linux/poll.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/slab.h">linux/slab.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/sched.h">linux/sched.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/types.h">linux/types.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/uio.h">linux/uio.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/uaccess.h">linux/uaccess.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/module.h">linux/module.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/linux/compat.h">linux/compat.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/sound/core.h">sound/core.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/sound/initval.h">sound/initval.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/sound/info.h">sound/info.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/sound/compress_params.h">sound/compress_params.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/sound/compress_offload.h">sound/compress_offload.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>
<span class="cp">#include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="cpf">&lt;<a href="v6.0/source/include/sound/compress_driver.h">sound/compress_driver.h</a>&gt;</span><span class="cp"></span>

<span class="cm">/* struct snd_compr_codec_caps overflows the ioctl bit size for some</span>
<span class="cm"> * architectures, so we need to disable the relevant ioctls.</span>
<span class="cm"> */</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="cp">#if <a href="v6.0/C/ident/_IOC_SIZEBITS">_IOC_SIZEBITS</a> &lt; 14</span>
<span class="cp">#define <a href="v6.0/C/ident/COMPR_CODEC_CAPS_OVERFLOW">COMPR_CODEC_CAPS_OVERFLOW</a></span>
<span class="cp">#endif</span>

<span class="cm">/* TODO:</span>
<span class="cm"> * - add substream support for multiple devices in case of</span>
<span class="cm"> *	SND_DYNAMIC_MINORS is not used</span>
<span class="cm"> * - Multiple node representation</span>
<span class="cm"> *	driver should be able to register multiple nodes</span>
<span class="cm"> */</span><span class="w"></span>

<span class="k">struct</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/snd_compr_file">snd_compr_file</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="p">{</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="w">	</span><span class="kt">unsigned</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="kt">long</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/caps">caps</a></span><span class="p">;</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="w">	</span><span class="k">struct</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/snd_compr_stream">snd_compr_stream</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/stream">stream</a></span><span class="p">;</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="p">};</span><span class="w"></span>

<span class="k">static</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="kt">void</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nf"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/error_delayed_work">error_delayed_work</a></span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">struct</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/work_struct">work_struct</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/work">work</a></span><span class="p">);</span><span class="w"></span>

<span class="cm">/*</span>
<span class="cm"> * a note on stream states used:</span>
<span class="cm"> * we use following states in the compressed core</span>
<span class="cm"> * SNDRV_PCM_STATE_OPEN: When stream has been opened.</span>
<span class="cm"> * SNDRV_PCM_STATE_SETUP: When stream has been initialized. This is done by</span>
<span class="cm"> *	calling SNDRV_COMPRESS_SET_PARAMS. Running streams will come to this</span>
<span class="cm"> *	state at stop by calling SNDRV_COMPRESS_STOP, or at end of drain.</span>
<span class="cm"> * SNDRV_PCM_STATE_PREPARED: When a stream has been written to (for</span>
<span class="cm"> *	playback only). User after setting up stream writes the data buffer</span>
<span class="cm"> *	before starting the stream.</span>
<span class="cm"> * SNDRV_PCM_STATE_RUNNING: When stream has been started and is</span>
<span class="cm"> *	decoding/encoding and rendering/capturing data.</span>
<span class="cm"> * SNDRV_PCM_STATE_DRAINING: When stream is draining current data. This is done</span>
<span class="cm"> *	by calling SNDRV_COMPRESS_DRAIN.</span>
<span class="cm"> * SNDRV_PCM_STATE_PAUSED: When stream is paused. This is done by calling</span>
<span class="cm"> *	SNDRV_COMPRESS_PAUSE. It can be stopped or resumed by calling</span>
<span class="cm"> *	SNDRV_COMPRESS_STOP or SNDRV_COMPRESS_RESUME respectively.</span>
<span class="cm"> */</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="k">static</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="kt">int</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nf"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/snd_compr_open">snd_compr_open</a></span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">struct</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/inode">inode</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/inode">inode</a></span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="k">struct</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/file">file</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="p">{</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="w">	</span><span class="k">struct</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/snd_compr">snd_compr</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/compr">compr</a></span><span class="p">;</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="w">	</span><span class="k">struct</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/snd_compr_file">snd_compr_file</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">;</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="w">	</span><span class="k">struct</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/snd_compr_runtime">snd_compr_runtime</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/runtime">runtime</a></span><span class="p">;</span><span class="w"></span>
<span class="w">	</span><span class="k">enum</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/snd_compr_direction">snd_compr_direction</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/dirn">dirn</a></span><span class="p">;</span><span class="w"></span>

<span class="w">		</span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/dirn">dirn</a></span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n"><a href="v6.0/C/ident/SND_COMPRESS_PLAYBACK">SND_COMPRESS_PLAYBACK</a></span><span class="p">;</span><span class="w"></span>
